.TH UTILITYKIT 1 "July 2026" "UtilityKit v5.10.6" "UtilityKit Tools"
.SH NAME
utility-markdown_toc \- Generate or refresh a table of contents in a markdown file based on its headings, validate relative links, and align pipe tables.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B utility markdown_toc
[\fIoptions\fP]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Generate or refresh a table of contents in a markdown file based on its headings, validate relative links, and align pipe tables.
.SH FEATURES
.PP
.IP \(bu 4
\fBTOC generation\fP — scans headings and inserts a linked table of contents with correct anchor slugs
.IP \(bu 4
\fBTOC refresh\fP — if markers already exist in the file the TOC is updated in place without disrupting surrounding content
.IP \(bu 4
\fBRelative link validation\fP — checks that every relative link in the file points to an existing file
.IP \(bu 4
\fBTable alignment\fP — pads pipe table columns so they line up cleanly
.IP \(bu 4
\fBDry-run by default\fP — previews all changes without writing to the file
.IP \(bu 4
\fBInteractive mode\fP — running without arguments launches a guided prompt
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH USAGE
.PP
.EX
bash _markdown_toc/_markdown_toc.sh

bash _markdown_toc/_markdown_toc.sh README.md

bash _markdown_toc/_markdown_toc.sh README.md --apply

bash _markdown_toc/_markdown_toc.sh README.md --apply --check-links

bash _markdown_toc/_markdown_toc.sh README.md --apply --align-tables

bash _markdown_toc/_markdown_toc.sh README.md --apply --check-links --align-tables
.EE
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
Option   |   Description
\fCFILE\fP   |   Markdown file to process
\fC--apply\fP   |   Write changes to the file (dry-run preview if omitted)
\fC--check-links\fP   |   Validate all relative links in the file
\fC--align-tables\fP   |   Pad pipe table columns for visual alignment
\fC-h, --help\fP   |   Show usage
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH TOC MARKERS
.PP
The tool uses HTML comment markers to track where the TOC lives in the file:
.PP
.EX
<!-- utilitykit:toc:start -->
- [Features](#features)
- [Usage](#usage)
- [Options](#options)
<!-- utilitykit:toc:end -->
.EE
.PP
On the first run the markers and TOC are inserted automatically after the first \fC#\fP heading. On subsequent runs the content between the markers is replaced with a freshly generated TOC.
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH ANCHOR SLUG RULES
.PP
Heading anchors are generated using the same rules GitHub Markdown uses:
.PP
.IP \(bu 4
Converted to lowercase
.IP \(bu 4
Spaces replaced with hyphens
.IP \(bu 4
Non-alphanumeric characters removed
.IP \(bu 4
Leading and trailing hyphens stripped
.PP
For example \fC## My Cool Section!\fP becomes \fC#my-cool-section\fP.
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH LINK VALIDATION OUTPUT
.PP
.EX
  Relative link validation
  ------------------------------------------------
  OK    docs/guide.md
  OK    CONTRIBUTING.md
  MISS  docs/missing-file.md
.EE
.PP
\fCOK\fP means the target file exists. \fCMISS\fP means it does not — useful for catching broken documentation links before pushing.
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH TABLE ALIGNMENT
.PP
Before:
.PP
.EX
| Name | Version | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| bash | 5.2 | required |
| python3 | 3.10 | optional |
.EE
.PP
After \fC--align-tables\fP:
.PP
.EX
| Name    | Version | Notes    |
| ------- | ------- | -------- |
| bash    | 5.2     | required |
| python3 | 3.10    | optional |
.EE
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH REQUIREMENTS
.PP
.IP \(bu 4
\fCpython3\fP — used for link validation and table alignment
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH EXIT CODES
.PP
Code   |   Meaning
\fC0\fP   |   Success
\fC1\fP   |   No file specified
